This paper deals with the analysis of dependency structures in natural language processing, which is a core topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves the analysis of network properties such as degree variance and the 2nd moment of degree, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and network science (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the memory cost of sentences, which can be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the study involves the analysis of relationships between different metrics, which can be related to graph theory (cs.CC).
